{"questionId":"14655","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The population of fish in a lake is modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( t \\right) = \\frac{{1000}}{{1 + 24{{\\text{e}}^{ - 0.2t}}}}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>24</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>e</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>0.2</mn>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>, 0&nbsp;≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤ 30 , where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> is measured in months.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the population of fish at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> = 10.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>(10)</p>\n<p>235.402</p>\n<p>235 (fish) (must be an integer) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14655","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.S_5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathemati